He was addressing the Intergovernmental Conference on an international legally binding instrument under the United Nations Convention on the Law of the Sea in order to protect a larger percentage of the globe's seas by 2030. 

The intergovernmental conference will meet over the next two weeks, the third of four treaty drafting sessions that seeks to conclude an instrument that will govern the conservation and use of plants and animals in the 64% of the world's seas that do not come under national jurisdiction. 

Sherwin Bryce-Pease reports… --SABC--